text: Jeff Saibene (born 13 September 1968) is a Luxembourgian former professional footballer. == Personal life == Saibene is a citizen of both Luxembourg and Switzerland and married with a Swiss wife. He is a fan of Hamburger SV. == Coaching career == Saibene was the manager of FC Aarau, in SwitzerlandProfile – FC Aarau and assistant to Allan Simonsen at the national team. He was formerly the assistant manager to Ryszard Komornicki at Aarau but was promoted in June 2009 when Komornicki left the club.Komornicki nicht mehr Trainer des FC Aarau He then managed Luxembourg U-21. He left his position in March 2011 to coach FC St. Gallen. On 19 March 2017, he was hired as the new head coach of Arminia Bielefeld. He was sacked on 10 December 2018. He was hired as the new head coach of FC Ingolstadt for the 2019–20 season. He was sacked on 9 March 2020. On 2 October 2020, he was hired as head coach of 1. FC Kaiserslautern. He was sacked on 30 January 2021. In June 2021, he was hired as head coach of Racing FC Union Luxembourg. ==Honours== ===As player=== Union Luxembourg * Luxembourg Cup: 1985–86 FC Aarau * Swiss National League A: 1992–93 ===As manager=== St. Gallen * Swiss Challenge League: 2011–12 Racing Union * Luxembourg Cup: 2021–22 == References == == Other websites == * * Player profile – Standard Liège Category:1968 births Category:Living people Category:Luxembourgian footballers Category:Arminia Bielefeld managers Category:Association football midfielders Category:FC Aarau managers Category:FC Thun managers Category:FC St. Gallen managers Category:1.
